{
  "brand": "Christie",
  "device": "PROJECTOR",
  "variant": "Christie E Series / DWU / DHD (ASCII '(CMD)' protocol)",
  "controlType": "RS232",
  "notes": [
    "Source: 'E Series Serial Commands Technical Reference Information' (Christie 020-000372-05 rev 1, 2011).",
    "Wire: D-Sub 9-pin null-modem (pin 2-3 cross, pin 5 GND). 115200 8N1 default, no flow control. Also supports 2400/4800/9600/14400/19200/38400/57600 via (BDR) menu.",
    "Format: ASCII command framed by '(' and ')'. Set: '(CMD<value>)'. Get: '(CMD?)'. Reply: '(CMD!<value>)'. No CR/LF needed — the parens delimit.",
    "SOURCE (SIN) codes: 0=VGA1, 1=VGA2, 2=BNC, 3=HDMI1, 4=HDMI2, 5=Component, 6=S-Video, 7=Composite.",
    "(KEY n) sends a remote keycode (decimal): 0=POWER, 19=MENU, 20=EXIT, 38=UP, 42=DOWN, 39=LEFT, 41=RIGHT, 40=ENTER, 47=AUTO, 48=INPUT, 49=OSD, 65=HOT KEY, 2=SHUTTER, 1=TEST.",
    "Query responses arrive as '(CMD!value)'. (PWR?) -> '(PWR!000)'=Off, '(PWR!001)'=On, '(PWR!010)'=Power-Up, '(PWR!011)'=Power-Down. (SIN?) -> '(SIN!003)' for HDMI1. (LPH?) -> '(LPH!01234)' lamp hours. (SST?) -> system status bitfield (alarms/errors). (SNO?) -> '(SNO!ABC1234)' serial. (VER+SOFT?) -> software version string. (BRT?)/(CON?) -> 0-1000 value. (SZP?) -> aspect: 0=Auto/1=Native/2=4:3/3=Letterbox/4=Full/5=FullWidth/6=FullHeight. (SHU?) -> '0'=Open/'1'=Closed."
  ],
